description:
## Why
The current audit logger only records run_command events. When a smoke test fails or a flow behaves unexpectedly, there is no way to reconstruct why the state machine took a particular path. Capture attempts, condition evaluations, and ask-judgment outcomes are invisible.

## What
Extend the AuditLogger port with new event types:
- capture_attempt: {varName, promptText, attempt}
- capture_result: {varName, success, value (truncated), failureReason}
- condition_evaluated: {condition, variables, result, method: 'variable'|'command'}
- judgment_emitted: {nodeId, question, groundedBy}
- judgment_result: {nodeId, verdict, rawValue}
- spawn_event: {childName, event: 'launched'|'polled'|'completed'|'failed'}

All appended to .prompt-language/audit.jsonl (already exists). Read-only — never replayed. Zero behavior impact.

Key files: src/application/ports/audit-logger.ts, src/infrastructure/adapters/file-audit-logger.ts, src/application/advance-flow.ts (call sites).

## Acceptance criteria
- AuditLogger port has new event type methods
- All new events logged at appropriate call sites
- Existing run_command logging unchanged
- JSONL entries have consistent schema
- Unit tests for new log event types
